#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:258
msgid ""
"Run the command :option:`traffic_ctl config reload` to apply the new "
"ticket key."
msgstr ""

# adfe597163ac401d91d8ed39f64da5da
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:261
msgid "OCSP Stapling"
msgstr ""

# 1f254a9bd9304ad8a05e341dbd648eac
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:263
msgid ""
"OCSP Stapling is an alternative approach to checking the revocation "
"status of an SSL certificate using the Online Certificate Status "
"Protocol."
msgstr ""

# b857b3b1b69348bca5d92ce0739aee41
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:267
msgid ""
"Under the original OCSP implementation, clients requested a certificate's"
" revocation status directly from the Certificate Authority (CA) that "
"issued the certificate.  This could cause significant load on the CA "
"servers since they were required to provide a response to every client of"
" a given certificate in real time."
msgstr ""

# 211bc7b112614b01983cc99a0b9a7855
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:274
msgid ""
"Enabling OCSP Stapling instructs Traffic Server to retrieve and cache the"
" revocation status of all configured SSL certificates, and present them "
"to the client when the client requests the status.  Traffic Server will "
"automatically query the OCSP responder specified in the SSL certificate "
"to gather the latest revocation status.  Traffic Server will then cache "
"the results for each configured certifcate.  The location of the OCSP "
"responder is taken from the Authority Information Access field of the "
"signed certificate. For example::"
msgstr ""

# ce60771243d140bfa1e40d672ca1efe6
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:286
msgid ""
"Support for OCSP Stapling can be tested using the -status option of the "
"OpenSSL client::"
msgstr ""

# e12305ea1ad342e8a74487aa5e7715be
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:297
msgid "Details of the OCSP Stapling TLS extension can be found in :rfc:`6961`."
msgstr ""

# ae85dc08aa924a97a95cc39cb465ae87
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:299
msgid ""
"To configure Traffic Server to use OCSP Stapling, edit the following "
"variables in :file:`records.config` file:"
msgstr ""

# b8e65045a2154327830fce539a2de983
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:302
msgid ":ts:cv:`proxy.config.ssl.ocsp.enabled`"
msgstr ""

# 8700943af06f4a32b7a06767bcbf5715
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:303
msgid ":ts:cv:`proxy.config.ssl.ocsp.cache_timeout`"
msgstr ""

# cb059aa8e6e840f79e92cf3b4a8daef2
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:304
msgid ":ts:cv:`proxy.config.ssl.ocsp.request_timeout`"
msgstr ""

# 3223ba9cc11147b0a76c4fe549e6ee0f
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:305
msgid ":ts:cv:`proxy.config.ssl.ocsp.update_period`"
msgstr ""

# a0435d325d7a480aa8ecdb5262f1827c
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:310
msgid "Split DNS"
msgstr ""

# 8264747c71a84ffb9ba9ae0dc1750110
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:312
msgid ""
"The *Split DNS* option enables you to configure Traffic Server to use "
"multiple DNS servers, as dictated by your security requirements. For "
"example, you might configure Traffic Server to use one set of DNS servers"
" to resolve hostnames on your internal network, while allowing DNS "
"servers outside the firewall to resolve hosts on the Internet. This "
"maintains the security of your intranet, while continuing to provide "
"direct access to sites outside your organization."
msgstr ""

# 3d2391902a334296b9924d1b06938be2
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:320
msgid "To configure Split DNS:"
msgstr ""

# 9e717e2a30e94c2b9876bc96615ad318
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:322
msgid ""
"Specify the rules for performing DNS server selection based on the "
"destination domain, the destination host, or a URL regular expression. "
"These rules are located in :file:`splitdns.config`."
msgstr ""

# e28ee7e30f1546bb89b32a9a7b7ce928
#: ../../admin-guide/security/index.en.rst:326
msgid ""
"Enable the *Split DNS* option by adjusting "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.dns.splitDNS.enabled` in :file:`records.config`. ::"
msgstr ""

